<h1>Problem 1257 - 2019 IMOSL, G2, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute-angled triangle and let \(D, E\), and \(F\) be the feet of altitudes from \(A, B\), and \(C\) to sides \(BC, CA\), and \(AB\), respectively. Denote by \(\omega_B\) and \(\omega_C\) the incircles of triangles \(BDF\) and \(CDE\), and let these circles be tangent to segments \(DF\) and \(DE\) at \(M\) and \(N\), respectively. Let line \(MN\) meet circles \(\omega_B\) and \(\omega_C\) again at \(P \ne M\) and \(Q \ne N\), respectively. Prove that \(MP = NQ\).</p>
